{{ if .OLMVersion -}}Version: {{ .OLMVersion }}{{ end }}
Namespace: {{ .Namespace }}

{{ if .HasInstallFiles -}}
**Prerequisites:** This component requires an OLM-enabled cluster (OpenShift or Kubernetes with OLM installed).

## Step 1: Deploy OLM Resources

```bash
# Create namespace
kubectl create namespace {{ .Namespace }} --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -

# Apply OLM installation manifests (Subscription, OperatorGroup, etc.)
{{ range .InstallFiles -}}
kubectl apply -f {{ .Path }}
{{ end -}}
```

## Step 2: Wait for Operator Ready

```bash
# Wait for operator ClusterServiceVersion to reach Succeeded phase
kubectl wait --for=condition=Succeeded csv \
  -l operators.coreos.com/{{ .OLMPackage }}.{{ .Namespace }} \
  -n {{ .Namespace }} \
  --timeout=5m
```

{{ if ne (len .CustomResources) 0 -}}
## Step 3: Deploy Custom Resources

```bash
# Apply custom resources
kubectl apply -f resources.yaml -n {{ .Namespace }}
```
{{ end -}}
{{ else -}}
**Prerequisites:** This component requires an OLM operator to be pre-installed in the cluster.

## Deploy

```bash
# Create namespace
kubectl create namespace {{ .Namespace }} --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -

# Apply custom resources
kubectl apply -f resources.yaml -n {{ .Namespace }}
```
{{ end -}}

## Verify

```bash
{{ if .HasInstallFiles -}}
# Check operator installation
kubectl get csv -n {{ .Namespace }}
{{ if ne (len .CustomResources) 0 -}}
# Check custom resources
kubectl get -f resources.yaml -n {{ .Namespace }}
{{ end -}}
{{ else -}}
# Check custom resources
kubectl get -f resources.yaml -n {{ .Namespace }}
{{ end -}}
```

## Undeploy

```bash
{{ if .HasInstallFiles -}}
{{ if ne (len .CustomResources) 0 -}}
# Delete custom resources first
kubectl delete -f resources.yaml -n {{ .Namespace }} --ignore-not-found
{{ end -}}
# Delete OLM resources
{{ range .InstallFiles -}}
kubectl delete -f {{ .Path }} --ignore-not-found
{{ end -}}
{{ else -}}
# Delete custom resources
kubectl delete -f resources.yaml -n {{ .Namespace }} --ignore-not-found
{{ end -}}
```
